dnata
05 May 2014 01:49 PM - UAE
. Job PurposeAs Airline Partnership Manager you will be responsible for planning, and managing the operation and expansion of dnata's  airline representation business in the region and  to ensure achievement of market share, revenue & contribution targets through dynamic management & representation of GSA airlines.  You will need to implement the business strategy and related policies for the department , whilst ensuring maximum profitability and productivity. Liaise with the Airline Principals to develop, manage and implement their business plans. Analysis of current agreements to seek opportunities to enhance the commercial relationship. You  would also be required to monitor changing market situations, and continuously adapt the business strategy to meet the environmental conditions and challenges of the future. Strong people management skills would be required to train, motivate and develop the team to be fit for the future.  Qualifications & Experience   Degree or Honours (12+3 or equivalent) Minimum of 8 years in Customer Service.Relationship Management Experience at a middle management capacity in an airline or a travel based organisation, with expertise in managing GSA travel trade related business . Knowledge  of airline policies and procedures,CRM and strategic management Familiarity with the Gulf travel business environment is desirable to understand customer needs and supplier capability.Salary & Benefits: We offer an attractive tax-free salary, paid in Dirhams, the local currency of the UAE. Besides generous travel benefits normally associated with an airline,this managerial role also has excellent leave, health care packages, accommodation and more. To Apply: Please submit your application before 3rd June 2014 23:59 GMT + 3 hours About dnata At dnata, our style of delighting customers is unique. That's why we attract the best people in the industry - people who can apply imagination to their work. We are growing quickly - and we are looking for people to join our global family of 20,000 employees. As the fourth largest combined air services provider, our services on the ground keep the world in the air. You'll find dnata in 38 countries offering customers our expertise in ground handling, cargo, travel, and flight catering.We believe in the power of our people - and we're always on the look-out for potential stars to h (more...)
